---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-egypt', text: 'Leaving Egyptian Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'destination-considerations', text: 'Destination Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best Gulf Region Insurance', href: '/best/gulf-region-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'arabicSupport', header: 'Arabic Support' },
  { key: 'gulfNetwork', header: 'Gulf Network' },
  { key: 'egyptCoverage', header: 'Egypt Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', egyptCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$170/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', gulfNetwork: 'Excellent', egyptCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$190/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', arabicSupport: 'Limited', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', egyptCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$165/mo' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', arabicSupport: 'Yes', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', egyptCoverage: 'Included', price: '$175/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Egypt', arabicSupport: 'Full', gulfNetwork: 'Limited', egyptCoverage: 'Included', price: '$110/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Egyptian Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Egyptian expats. Find coverage for Gulf countries, Europe, the US, and other destinations."
  headline="Best Insurance for Egyptian Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Egyptian expats are concentrated in the Gulf, Europe, and North America. Here's how to stay protected abroad while maintaining coverage for visits home."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/egyptian-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Egyptian expats are found in significant numbers in the UAE, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, Germany, US, and other countries. Healthcare costs vary dramatically by destination. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Egyptian expats. Strong Gulf networks, Arabic support, comprehensive coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks. Arabic support available.</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> Good coverage with Egypt often included. Strong Gulf and European networks.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good global coverage at competitive prices.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Egypt:</strong> Local insurer with some international options. Full Arabic support, includes Egypt.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Gulf Employment Coverage"
    description="Many Gulf countries require employer-provided insurance. However, employer plans vary in quality and end with employment. Understand your employer coverage and consider supplemental insurance for better protection."
    buttonText="Compare Options"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-egypt">Leaving Egyptian Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Egypt has both public and private healthcare options. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>Universal Health Insurance (UHI)</h3>
  <p>
    Egypt is implementing a Universal Health Insurance system. Coverage is tied to Egyptian residence and registration. Moving abroad means this coverage doesn't follow you internationally.
  </p>

  <h3>Social Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Egyptian social insurance provides some healthcare benefits to contributing workers. This is tied to Egyptian employment and doesn't extend internationally.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Egyptian Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Egyptian companies (Allianz Egypt, AXA Egypt, MetLife Alico) typically provides limited international coverage—usually emergency treatment for short periods abroad. Long-term stays need dedicated international insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Returning for Treatment</h3>
  <p>
    Some Egyptian expats return to Egypt for medical treatment due to lower costs. International insurance that includes Egypt coverage allows this flexibility.
  </p>

  <h2 id="destination-considerations">Destination Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    Egyptian expats face different situations depending on destination:
  </p>

  <h3>Gulf Countries (UAE, Saudi, Kuwait, Qatar)</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Egyptian expat concentration. Employer-provided insurance is mandatory in most Gulf countries. However, employer plans vary significantly—some are comprehensive, others have major limitations. Supplemental insurance provides security.
  </p>

  <h3>Germany</h3>
  <p>
    Significant Egyptian community. German healthcare requires enrollment in the local system (GKV or PKV) for residents. International insurance covers transition periods.
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Growing Egyptian community, especially in New Jersey, California, and New York. US healthcare is extremely expensive—comprehensive coverage is essential.
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    NHS provides free healthcare to legal residents with proper visa status. Many Egyptian expats supplement NHS with private insurance for faster access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Currency Considerations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      The Egyptian pound has experienced significant devaluation. USD or EUR-denominated policies provide stability—your coverage maintains its value regardless of pound movements.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage ideal for Egyptian expats. Strong networks in the Gulf (largest diaspora region) and worldwide. Arabic support is available. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 service with Arabic capability. Egypt coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Egyptian expats who want reliable global coverage with Arabic support.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Arabic support available through their Middle East operations. Service quality is outstanding.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium positioning. Best for professionals who can afford top-tier coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Egyptian professionals who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>AXA Global</h3>
  <p>
    AXA has presence in Egypt (AXA Egypt) and globally. Their international products often include Egypt coverage automatically. Strong Gulf and European networks.
  </p>

  <p>
    Arabic support available. Good option for those who want seamless Egypt coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Egyptian expats who visit home frequently and want included Egypt coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in Europe and the Gulf. Arabic support is limited compared to regional specialists.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Egyptian expats seeking good value with global coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Egypt</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Egypt offers some international products for Egyptians abroad. Full Arabic service, familiar brand, Egypt coverage included. International networks are more limited than global insurers.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Egyptian expats who prefer familiar Egyptian service and primarily need Egypt coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="Get quotes from multiple providers to find the best balance of network strength, Arabic support, and price for your destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance needs vary by destination. Here's what Egyptian expats should consider:
  </p>

  <h3>United Arab Emirates</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Egyptian expat community. Health insurance is mandatory—employers must provide it. Dubai and Abu Dhabi have excellent healthcare facilities. Many Egyptian doctors practice in the UAE. Supplemental coverage ensures better benefits.
  </p>

  <h3>Saudi Arabia</h3>
  <p>
    Large Egyptian workforce. Employer-provided insurance is mandatory. Coverage quality varies—international insurance can supplement basic employer plans.
  </p>

  <h3>Kuwait</h3>
  <p>
    Significant Egyptian community. Public healthcare is available to residents but limited. Private insurance recommended for better access.
  </p>

  <h3>Germany</h3>
  <p>
    Growing Egyptian community. German healthcare system is comprehensive but requires enrollment. International insurance covers the transition and provides options.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Does Egyptian insurance cover me abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Egyptian insurance provides limited international coverage (emergency only, short periods). For living abroad, you need dedicated international health insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Gulf employer insurance enough?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Quality varies significantly. Some employer plans are comprehensive; others have limitations. Review your plan carefully and consider supplemental coverage for gaps.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Should I get USD or EGP coverage?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">USD or EUR is recommended. Egyptian pound volatility can erode coverage value. Hard currency policies maintain purchasing power.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Egypt visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">AXA and Allianz Egypt include Egypt coverage automatically. Other insurers offer Egypt as a coverage region. Confirm with your provider.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Arabic support available?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Cigna, Bupa, and AXA offer Arabic support through their Middle East operations. Egyptian insurers provide full Arabic service.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Are there Egyptian doctors in the Gulf?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Yes, many Egyptian doctors practice in the UAE, Saudi Arabia, and other Gulf countries. Your insurer covers any qualified doctor.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Egyptian expats need comprehensive international insurance—Egyptian coverage doesn't work abroad meaningfully. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is our top recommendation for strong Gulf coverage with Arabic support.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium coverage for those who can afford the best. <strong>AXA Global</strong> suits those who want included Egypt coverage. <strong>Allianz Egypt</strong> works for those preferring familiar Egyptian service.
  </p>

  <p>
    In the Gulf, don't rely solely on employer coverage—quality varies and it ends with employment. Choose hard currency coverage to protect against Egyptian pound volatility.
  </p>

</PageShell>
